Female officersâ€™ hair must not extend beyond the collar of the blouse or interfere with wearing of all official headgear and should not fall over the ears or on the forehead below the headband.Nails and make-up, female officers are obliged to keep their make-up subtle and discreet. Only natural and clear nail polish may be used; nail extensions are not be permitted and tattoos must be covered.Officers manning gender desks and Child Protection Units have been excluded from wearing uniform on duty, but they are still tied to the directive to keep their hair, make-up and body arts to the bare minimum.